## Truth-Seeking Agentic Debate System — Speed & Quality Optimization (2026-05-13)

### System Profile
- Python asyncio orchestrator, 4 workers, semaphore(10), kiro-cli subprocess per LLM call
- 721 agent calls, 7.2h wall time, 28h total compute, median 83s/call, max 5614s
- 48 resolved contentions (28 judged + 20 agreed), 46% "both_correct" waste
- Recursive depth up to 7, 56 child contentions spawned

### Root Causes (Confirmed)
1. kiro-cli subprocess has irreducible 15-20s latency floor (ACP protocol overhead). Cold start >60s. Cannot be reduced without replacing transport.
2. Depth explosion: MAX_DEPTH=7, MAX_EXCHANGES=7 → 7^7 = 823,543 theoretical max calls. 56 children spawned, mostly in rounds 1-2.
3. 46% both_correct waste: System debates complementary perspectives, not genuine contradictions. iMAD (AAAI 2026) confirms only 5-19% of cases benefit from debate.
4. 7 rounds causes quality degradation: EACL 2026 Problem Drift paper, sycophancy research (Yao 2025), RL termination research all confirm correct→incorrect flips outnumber incorrect→correct in later rounds.

### Key Contradiction Resolved
"Single-agent outperforms multi-agent" (Plumbing Not People, Amazon internal) vs "MAD improves accuracy" (iMAD)
- Resolution: Both correct in different contexts. Single-agent wins for general task completion. MAD wins for genuinely contested factual questions. The fix is selective triggering — pre-screen contentions, debate only when genuine contradiction exists. iMAD's own finding: only 5-19% of cases benefit from debate.

### Optimization Priority Order (20-55x combined speedup)
1. Replace kiro-cli with direct Bedrock API (boto3 invoke_model) — eliminates 15-20s floor, enables all other improvements. 1.6x per call minimum.
2. Config changes (2 min): MAX_DEPTH=3, MAX_EXCHANGES=4, RELEVANCE_THRESHOLD=0.85, MAX_CHILDREN_PER_NODE=2, MAX_TOTAL_CALLS=200
3. Parallel Team A + Team B via asyncio.gather() — each team gets previous round's opponent response. 1.7x on 81% of calls.
4. Selective pre-screening — 1 cheap call before debate: "are these positions genuinely contradictory?" If no, mark both_correct immediately. Eliminates 46% of contentions.
5. Prompt caching for ESTABLISHED TRUTHS section — use Claude Sonnet 4.5 for 1-hour TTL. Cache reads bypass TPM quota. 85% latency reduction, 90% cost reduction on cached tokens.
6. Conciseness constraint — "under 400 words" in all prompts + max_tokens=600. Reduces output token burn 4x.
7. Convergence detection after round 3 — check for convergence words in both sides' last responses.

### Prompt Caching Critical Details
- Bedrock EPC requires byte-for-byte match of prompt prefix — no dynamic content before cache marker
- Claude 3.7 Sonnet: 1024 token minimum, 5-min TTL (resets on hit)
- Claude Sonnet 4.5: 4096 token minimum, 1-hour TTL available
- Use single region (not CRIS) to maximize cache hits — CRIS routing degrades cache hit rate
- Cache reads bypass TPM quota entirely

### Academic Literature Key Papers
- iMAD (arxiv 2511.11306, AAAI 2026): selective triggering, 92% token reduction, 13.5% accuracy improvement
- Problem Drift (EACL 2026): 7 rounds causes degradation, not improvement
- Adaptive Stability Detection (arxiv 2510.12697, NeurIPS 2025): KS-statistic convergence detection
- D3/SAMRE (arxiv 2410.04663v2): MORE architecture (multi-advocate parallel) achieves 4-round quality in 1 round
- HCP-MAD (arxiv 2604.09679): 3-tier approach (independent → pair debate → collective vote)

### CloudWatch Gap
System has no CloudWatch integration — all metrics from flat debate.log file. To add observability: use CloudWatch Embedded Metrics Format (EMF) in acp.py to emit per-call latency automatically.
EOF
